---
title: Crispy Prosciutto & Peach Grain Bowls with Feta, Arugula, Lemon Dijon Dressing & Almonds
description: Sweet caramelized peach slices and crispy prosciutto strike the perfect balance of sweet and savory for these fresh and hearty grain bowls. Mixed grains are tossed with arugula and feta—plus the peaches and prosciutto—in a lemony peach dressing. A final shower of almonds, even more crispy prosciutto, and a squeeze of fresh lemon seal the deal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/686385850203e9f8dbb4c6c4-a0c7bd69.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/686385850203e9f8dbb4c6c4-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-prosciutto-and-peach-grain-bowls-686385850203e9f8dbb4c6c4
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 980 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve @peach{1} and remove pit; cut into 1⁄4-inch-thick slices. Toss peach slices in a #small bowl{} with @sugar{1/2%TBSP} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together garlic, lemon zest, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @peach jam{1%unit}, 1 TBSP @olive oil{1%TBSP}, juice from half the lemon, salt, and @pepper{}; set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add peach slices; cook until lightly browned and fork-tender, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Add 2 TBSP @water{2%TBSP}; cook, stirring, until liquid has thickened and is syrupy, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Remove from heat; stir in 1 TBSP @butter{1%TBSP}. Transfer to #bowl{} with dressing. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for peach over medium-high heat. Add @prosciutto{2%ounce} in a single layer; sear until browned and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (If prosciutto starts to crisp too quickly, reduce heat to medium.)

Turn off heat; transfer prosciutto to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop into bite-size pieces.

Meanwhile, massage @microwavable grain blend{1%unit} in package to separate grains. Partially open package; microwave until warmed through, ~{1 1/2-2%minutes}.

To bowl with caramelized peach and dressing, add grain blend, @arugula{2%ounce}, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and half the crispy prosciutto. Toss to combine.

Divide peach and grain salad between bowls. Top with @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and remaining crispy prosciutto. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Sweet caramelized peach slices and crispy prosciutto strike the perfect balance of sweet
> and savory for these fresh and hearty grain bowls. The peaches and prosciutto are
> featured both in the dressing and as a topping.